Deadlight — build log placeholder (macOS editor host)
=======================================================
This file documents the last editor build attempt on a Mac. Replace with real Unity
console output if your course requires proof of build.

If you only ship a Windows executable, add a sibling **build_windows.log** from the
machine that ran **Deadlight → Build Windows** (Unity menu).

Template — paste Editor.log excerpt after build:
--------------------------------------------------
Date:
Unity version:
Platform target:
Result (success / fail):
First error line (if any):

--------------------------------------------------
(Optional) Command-line batch build examples (adjust Unity path and project path):
  # macOS player smoke (project includes this method):
  .../Unity.app/Contents/MacOS/Unity -batchmode -nographics -quit \
    -projectPath "/path/to/deadlight" \
    -executeMethod Deadlight.Editor.DeadlightMenuItems.BuildMacHeadlessTest \
    -logFile ./tmp/unity_build.log

  # Windows .exe (requires Windows Build Support module):
  .../Unity.app/Contents/MacOS/Unity -batchmode -nographics -quit \
    -projectPath "/path/to/deadlight" \
    -executeMethod Deadlight.Editor.DeadlightMenuItems.BuildWindowsHeadlessTest \
    -logFile ./tmp/unity_build_windows.log
